50|$|A {{hoof pick}} or {{horseshoe}} nail can help remove the plug prior to insertion of a screw-in stud. A special instrument called a <b>T-tap</b> {{is used to}} clean out the stud holes before the stud is screwed in, or {{it can be used to}} re-tap the stud hole if the threads are damaged. Additionally, a small metal brush can be used to help clean threads which are especially dirty. A wrench is used to tighten or loosen the studs.|$|E

